main event: An observer reported seeing one unidentified flying object in Washington, D.C. on August 5, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for a total of 10 minutes,It initially appeared in the north and then quickly moved to the southwest,The observer noted it was giving off illumination during its rapid movement,The object was seen at a height and appeared red and yellow when it was high in the sky,The observer's belief that the object moved behind a cloud was unsubstantiated as the first sighting lasted only 2 seconds.
witness description: The observer was noted as a male, age 41, with a strong background in photography and familiarity with celestial phenomena.
